<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
<meta charset="UTF-8">
<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
<title>Beyond the Label | Food Reform Now</title>

<style>
body {
    margin: 0;
    font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
    background: #111;
    color: #fff;
}

header {
    background: linear-gradient(to right, #e63946, #ff6b6b);
    padding: 40px;
    text-align: center;
}

header h1 {
    font-size: 3rem;
}

.section {
    padding: 50px;
    max-width: 1000px;
    margin: auto;
}

.stat {
    font-size: 2rem;
    color: #ff6b6b;
    margin: 20px 0;
}

.quote {
    font-style: italic;
    border-left: 4px solid #ff6b6b;
    padding-left: 15px;
    margin: 20px 0;
}

.card {
    background: #222;
    padding: 25px;
    margin: 20px 0;
    border-radius: 10px;
}

button {
    background: #e63946;
    color: white;
    padding: 15px 30px;
    border: none;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    cursor: pointer;
    border-radius: 5px;
}

button:hover {
    background: #ff6b6b;
}

footer {
    text-align: center;
    padding: 20px;
    background: #000;
}
</style>
</head>

<body>

<header>
    <h1>Beyond the Label</h1>
    <p>The Hidden Health Crisis in Ultra-Processed Foods</p>
</header>

<div class="section">

    <h2>The Problem</h2>

    <div class="stat">Nearly 60% of the American diet = ultra-processed foods</div>
    <p>
        Ultra-processed foods dominate what Americans eat daily, exposing people to chemical additives over long periods of time.
    </p>

    <div class="quote">
        “Higher consumption of ultra-processed foods was associated with an increased risk of cancer.”  
        — British Medical Journal Study
    </div>

</div>

<div class="section">

    <h2>What Science Says</h2>

    <div class="card">
        <h3>Heart Disease & Diabetes</h3>
        <p>
            The American Heart Association reports diets high in ultra-processed foods are linked to:
        </p>
        <ul>
            <li>Obesity</li>
            <li>Hypertension</li>
            <li>Type 2 Diabetes</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h3>Hidden Chemical Risks</h3>
        <p>
            Research shows preservatives can contain unexpected chemical dangers like metal impurities, highlighting gaps in safety evaluations.
        </p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
        <h3>Children at Risk</h3>
        <p>
            Children are especially vulnerable due to their body size and consumption patterns.
        </p>

        <div class="quote">
            “Children are more vulnerable to food additive toxicity due to their lower body weight.”
            — Kraemer et al.
        </div>
    </div>

</div>

<div class="section">

    <h2>The Real Issue: Weak Regulation</h2>

    <p>
        The FDA allows companies to classify additives as safe without independent review through the GRAS loophole.
    </p>

    <div class="quote">
        “Manufacturers may conclude that a substance is GRAS and introduce it into food without FDA approval.”
        — FDA
    </div>

    <p>
        Experts argue current policies fail to address the combined effects of multiple additives consumed daily.
    </p>

    <div class="quote">
        “Ultra-processed foods are largely missing from U.S. food policy.”
        — Jennifer Pomeranz
    </div>

</div>

<div class="section">

    <h2>Global Comparison</h2>

    <p>
        Other countries like those in the European Union enforce stricter food safety laws.
        Companies already produce safer versions of products for those markets.
    </p>

    <div class="stat">Safer food is possible — it's already happening elsewhere</div>

</div>

<div class="section">

    <h2>Take Action</h2>

    <p>
        This is not just about food — it's about public health, children’s safety, and the future.
    </p>

    <ul>
        <li>Demand stricter FDA regulation</li>
        <li>Support clearer food labeling</li>
        <li>Reduce consumption of ultra-processed foods</li>
        <li>Raise awareness in your community</li>
    </ul>

    <button onclick="takeAction()">Join the Movement</button>

</div>

<footer>
    <p>Created to inspire change | Based on scientific research</p>
</footer>

<script>
function takeAction() {
    alert("You’ve taken the first step. Now share this and demand change.");
}
</script>

